Two people in Embu have been admitted in hosptial and tested positive for cholera. Embu health executive Dr Jamleck Muturi (pictured) said seven others have exhibited symptoms and are being treated. One cholera victim lives in the Grogon slums, while the other hails from Runyenjes. Muturi said the health department has isolated them. The two patients with cholera are responding well to treatment. Health workers are searching for the source. Food hawking has been banned in Grogon and some parts of Runyenjes.The families of victims have been supplied with aqua tabs to disinfect water. Cholera cases rise during the rainy season. Â 